description: Reproduction side cover grommet. This is typically used on side covers but it is also used other places such as the owners manual holder under the seat on the CB550. Unfortunately, side covers get cracked a lot, usually it''s due to improper installation and removal. Sometimes the side covers are hard to remove due to the old hard grommets. Install a new set and save your side covers from future cracks! Don''t forget to add some grease to the grommets and the tabs on the side covers for easy installation and removal.

When removing side covers we like to do it one tab at a time. If you do it slowly and carefully, using both hands, they shouldn''t crack. If you have side covers that have two slots on top, unlatch the seat, remove the bottom tab then the top two. It sounds so simple, yet so many side covers are cracked....
Note: This part is usually used on the side cover but some models used it in other places. Only some of the models listed below used 4 of these grommets.
